James Alasdair Duff (born 26 January 1989 in Inverness, Scotland) is a Scottish professional association football plays as a centre back for Rothes.
Duff broke into the Inverness Caledonian Thistle first team during the early part of the 2008–09 season, making his senior début in a 1–0 defeat by Hamilton Academical. He signed for Elgin City in 2010. Duff left Elgin after six years, signing for Highland Football League side Brora Rangers in November 2016.Duff represented the Scotland under–21 level team for the first time in a 3–1 defeat against Northern Ireland in November 2008.
